               <p>VALENTINE SCOTNEY. I am a <rs id="t18070218-3-viclabel16" type="occupation">linen draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070218-3-victim123 t18070218-3-viclabel16"></join>, <placeName id="t18070218-3-crimeloc17">No. 115, Oxford street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18070218-3-crimeloc17" type="placeName" value="No. 115, Oxford street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18070218-3-crimeloc17" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18070218-3-off14 t18070218-3-crimeloc17"></join>. On the 29th of January, I missed thirteen yards and a half of printed cotton. The next morning Seagoe the officer brought it me, and asked me if it was my property. It was hanging in the passage</p>
               <p>Q. Are you sure it was not sold. - A. I am confident it was not sold.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18070218-3-person124">
                  JOHN 
                  SEAGOE
               <interp inst="t18070218-3-person124" type="surname" value="SEAGOE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070218-3-person124" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18070218-3-person124" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . In taking the prisoner to the round house on the 29th of January, I searched her, I found this cotton upon her, here is the shop mark on it. I went to Mr. Scotney's in Oxford street; he said it was his.</p>
               <p>(The property produced and identified.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. You know you did not find it on me, I was not in the shop at all, nor was I in the passage. I did not take it</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18070218-3-verdict18" type="verdictDescription">
